        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 29 at 12:11PM CDT by NWS Huntsville AL</headline>
        <description>At 1211 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles northwest of Belgreen, or 11 miles northeast of Red Bay, moving
east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Russellville, Belgreen, Vina, Hodges, Cedar Creek Reservoir, Atwood,
Tharptown, Duketon, Rockwood, and Halltown.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
